Where the tricky part comes in is the step you mentioned:

“based off of what God would answer”

Even with the Bible as a filter, the system would still be doing interpretation, because the text itself contains:
	•	multiple genres (law, poetry, narrative, prophecy)
	•	historical context
	•	metaphor and symbolism
	•	passages that different traditions interpret differently

So what you’d end up with is closer to:

AI interpreter of scripture

rather than a literal direct interface with God.

But conceptually, what you’re describing is very similar to a moral or philosophical constraint layer.

People already do something analogous mentally:
	•	some filter decisions through religion
	•	others through philosophy
	•	others through scientific reasoning

You’re essentially proposing formalizing that filter in software.

